            <ce:figure id="f0005">
               <ce:label>Fig. 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cn0005">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0015" view="all">Study area. From North to South, Campaegli (Lat 41.97, Long 13.12, Alt 1460 m a.s.l.), Pennataro (Lat 41.73, Long 14.19, Alt 930 m a.s.l.) and Giffone (Lat 38.42, Long 16.18, Alt 984 m a.s.l.).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:link locator="gr1" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112721008719/gr1" id="lk00005"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:figure id="f0010">
               <ce:label>Fig. 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cn0010">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0020" view="all">Sensitivity analysis of Occurrence (sx) and Richness (dx) considering three forest management systems: unmanaged, close-to-nature, and combined in Campaegli (CA), Bosco Pennataro (BP), and Giffone (GF). The x-variable was selected based on the most significant variable of the models, which are DBH and H for occurrence and richness respectively.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:link locator="gr2" xlink:type="simple" xlink:role="http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4" xlink:href="pii:S0378112721008719/gr2" id="lk00010"/>
            </ce:figure>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" frame="topbot" id="t0005" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
               <ce:label>Table 1</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cn0015">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">List and description of the tree structural parameters as collected in the field (a) or calculated (b) and used in this study, and definition of the Tree-related Microhabitat (TreMs) occurrence, richness and TreM-tree adopted in this study.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <tgroup cols="4">
                  <colspec colname="col1" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col2" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col3" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col4" align="left"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1" valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">
                           <bold>Structural parameters&amp; definition</bold>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">
                           <bold>Acronym</bold>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">
                           <bold>Unit</bold>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">
                           <bold>Description</bold>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Diameter at breast height<sup loc="post">a</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">DBH</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">cm</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">The diameter of trees measured at breast height</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Tree height<sup loc="post">a</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">H</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Total height of the trees</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Crown projection area<sup loc="post">a</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">CPA</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m<sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">The surface of horizontal area of tree crown</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Crown base<sup loc="post">a</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">CB</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Height of the trunk at the first attached living branch</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Crown length<sup loc="post">b</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">CL</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Length of the tree crown, obtained by H-CB</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Live-to-crown ratio<sup loc="post">b</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">LCR</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">–</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Ratio between crown length and total height</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Slenderness coefficient<sup loc="post">b</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">SL</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">–</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Ratio between tree height and DBH</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Basal Area<sup loc="post">b</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">BA</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m<sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">The cross-sectional area of the stem at breast height</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Growing stock<sup loc="post">b</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">V</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">m<sup loc="post">3</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Volume (m<sup loc="post">3</sup>) of trunk and large branches (diameter &gt; 5 cm) (<cross-ref refid="b0315" id="c0005">Tabacchi et al., 2011</cross-ref>)</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Tree-related Microhabitats occurrence</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">TreMs occurrence</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">no.</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">The presence of at least one tree-related microhabitat (TreM) on a tree, according to the field list developed by (<cross-ref refid="b0145" id="c0010">Kraus et al., 2016</cross-ref>)</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Tree-related Microhabitats richness</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">TreMs richness</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">no.</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">The presence of 1 or more types of TreMs on a tree, according to the field list developed by (<cross-ref refid="b0145" id="c0015">Kraus et al., 2016</cross-ref>) which reports a total of 64 TreM types.</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Tree bearing TreMs</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">TreM-tree</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">no.</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" align="center">Living trees bearing at least one TreM as in (<cross-ref refid="b0195" id="c0020">Martin et al., 2021</cross-ref>).</entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </ce:table>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" frame="topbot" id="t0010" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
               <ce:label>Table 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cn0020">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0030" view="all">Summary of stand structural characteristics (basal area (BA), volume (V), tree height (H), diameter at breast height (DBH), Crown Projection Area (CPA) and Slenderness Coefficient (SL)) of the study areas: Bosco Pennataro (BP), Giffone (GF) and Campaegli (CA). Data are summarised for all trees (tot), only Tree bearing TreMs (TreM-tree) and only Trees without TreMs (T). In this study we consider TreM-tree each tree that bears at least one TreM. Further details about forest structure (i.e., DBH and H distribution) are reported in the supplementary material- Annex 1.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
