            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" frame="topbot" id="t0015" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
               <ce:label>Table 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cn0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0040" view="all">GLM results for TreMs occurrence (left column) and richness (right column). The variables used are sites (GF = Giffone; CA = Campaegli. Bosco Pennataro is not visible because is the reference category), height (H), diameter at breast height (DBH), crown projection area (CPA), crown base (CB), crown length (CL = H - CB), live-to-crown ratio (LCR = CL H-1), slenderness coefficient (SL = H DBH-1), basal area (BA) and the volume (V). The best fitting models are in bold and italic. Significance value: ***(p &lt; 0.001); **(p &lt; 0.01); *(p &lt; 0.05).</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <tgroup cols="7">
                  <colspec colname="col1" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col2" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col3" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col4" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col5" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col6" align="left"/>
                  <colspec colname="col7" align="left"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1" valign="top">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Model</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Predictors</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">AIC</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">R<sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Predictors</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">AIC</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">R<sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row valign="top">
